content: I think if you look at it from a sequential perspective, you got to remember in this environment, there's always going to be puts and takes from one quarter to the next, either related to seasonality, which drives the difference in regional mix, differences in product mix. And remember what I said, in this environment, especially the predictability around what we're going to get for things that I would call fulfillment versus things that I would call related to design win and demand creation tends to vary a bit as well.
